Basic MongoDB Concepts

Database â†’ Collection â†’ Document

Database = like a folder

Collection = like a table

Document = JSON-like object

Example document:

{
  "name": "Rahul",
  "age": 21,
  "course": "BCA"
}

2ï¸âƒ£ CRUD Operations in MongoDB

CRUD = Create, Read, Update, Delete

ðŸ”¹ CREATE (Insert Data)
Insert One Document
db.students.insertOne({
  name: "Amit",
  age: 22,
  course: "BCA"
})

Insert Multiple Documents
db.students.insertMany([
  { name: "Riya", age: 21 },
  { name: "Neha", age: 23 }
])

ðŸ”¹ READ (Fetch Data)
Find All Documents
db.students.find()

Find with Condition
db.students.find({ age: 22 })

Find One Document
db.students.findOne({ name: "Amit" })

Projection (Select Fields)
db.students.find({}, { name: 1, _id: 0 })

ðŸ”¹ UPDATE (Modify Data)
Update One
db.students.updateOne(
  { name: "Amit" },
  { $set: { age: 23 } }
)

Update Many
db.students.updateMany(
  { course: "BCA" },
  { $set: { status: "active" } }
)

Increment Value
db.students.updateOne(
  { name: "Amit" },
  { $inc: { age: 1 } }
)

ðŸ”¹ DELETE (Remove Data)
Delete One
db.students.deleteOne({ name: "Amit" })

Delete Many
db.students.deleteMany({ course: "BCA" })

3ï¸âƒ£ Query Operators (Important for Viva)
Comparison Operators
$eq   $ne   $gt   $lt   $gte   $lte


Example:

db.students.find({ age: { $gt: 20 } })

Logical Operators
$and   $or   $not


Example:

db.students.find({
  $and: [{ age: { $gt: 20 } }, { course: "BCA" }]
})

4ï¸âƒ£ Sorting, Limiting, Counting
Sort
db.students.find().sort({ age: 1 })   // Ascending

Limit
db.students.find().limit(5)

Count
db.students.countDocuments()

5ï¸âƒ£ MongoDB with MERN (Node.js Example)
const mongoose = require("mongoose")

mongoose.connect("mongodb://localhost:27017/collegeDB")
.then(() => console.log("MongoDB Connected"))
.catch(err => console.log(err))
